  "prompt": "How can I manage inbox in outlook for rapid response when I have a email flow of 200 emails per day?",
  "response": "Managing a high-volume email inbox in Outlook can be challenging. Here are some strategies to help you handle 200 emails per day efficiently:\n\n1. Use Folders and Rules\n- Create automatic sorting rules\n- Categorize emails by sender, subject, or keywords\n- Move non-urgent emails to specific folders\n\n2. Leverage Outlook's Quick Steps\n- Create custom actions for rapid processing\n- Set up one-click moves, flags, or replies\n- Automate repetitive tasks\n\n3. Use Inbox Zero Approach\n- Process emails immediately\n- Decide: Reply, Delete, Delegate, or File\n- Aim to keep inbox empty\n\n4. Utilize Flags and Categories\n- Flag urgent emails\n- Color-code by priority\n- Set follow-up reminders\n\n5. Use Search and Filter Functions\n- Quick search capabilities\n- Advanced filters\n- Find emails rapidly\n\n6. Implement Time Blocking\n- Dedicated email processing times\n- 2-3 specific slots per day\n- Avoid constant interruptions\n\n7. Outlook Focused Inbox\n- Automatically separates important emails\n- Prioritizes key messages\n- Reduces distraction\n\n8. Consider Add-ins\n- Boomerang\n- SaneBox\n- Help manage email workflow\n\n9. Use Quick Parts and Templates\n- Save standard responses\n- Reduce typing time\n- Maintain consistency",
